			<title>The Year in Review: What was your favorite game of 2015?</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?78350-The-Year-in-Review-What-was-your-favorite-game-of-2015&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Mon, 28 Dec 2015 07:58:09 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[2015 is almost over, but before we look forward to what 2016 will bring us, let's look back and appreciate what we enjoyed the most in 2015. 
 
It can be anything you played, whether it came out this year or not, though you may still want to make the distinction. I played a heck load of games this...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>2015 is almost over, but before we look forward to what 2016 will bring us, let's look back and appreciate what we enjoyed the most in 2015.<br />
<br />
It can be anything you played, whether it came out this year or not, though you may still want to make the distinction. I played a heck load of games this year, and actually spent most of my time trying to catch up on what I missed rather than playing new games, so I'm going to cheat and do both.<br />
<br />
My favorite games released in 2015 were:<br />
<br />
1) Ori and the Blind Forest - I almost forgot about this one, as it was earlier in the year. It was very nearly my perfect game. Great pacing with a good amount of content.<br />
2) Batman: Arkham Knight - I got lucky and it actually ran on my PC (after they &quot;fixed&quot; it). Much like Ori, it was exactly what I needed it to be, with only the Riddler trophies marring the package.<br />
<br />
My favorite games played in 2015, but released previously:<br />
<br />
1) The Witcher 1/2 - I had these in the backlog and never made time for them before now. Great games. It's hard to say if I liked them more than the two above or not.<br />
2) Danganronpa 1/2 - Very niche. Scratched an itch I didn't know needed scratching. Once I got past the weird character designs I found it to be engrossing.<br />
<br />
<br />
There were a number of things I missed or didn't have time for. Witcher 3 being the forefront of the list. Judging by how much I liked the previous two, it probably would have gotten a mention as well. I've also yet to get a Wii U, despite it having an even better year than last year.</div>

]]></content:encoded>
