			<title><![CDATA[[Consoles] Which console should I buy?]]></title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?78311-Consoles-Which-console-should-I-buy&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Sun, 06 Dec 2015 18:12:32 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>We are discussing get a game console for Christmas. This plus a game or two would be *the* present under the tree, nothing else but stocking stuffers, and we want to get it right. 
 
The last console we had, which was lost in the epic flooding of 2013, was a Wii for playing goofy games with the...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>We are discussing get a game console for Christmas. This plus a game or two would be *the* present under the tree, nothing else but stocking stuffers, and we want to get it right.<br />
<br />
The last console we had, which was lost in the epic flooding of 2013, was a Wii for playing goofy games with the extended family. Years before that we had a PS2 which mainly gathered dust. We aren't really console people.<br />
<br />
However our daughter, H, is 6 and is showing a lot of interest in computer games, especially SWOTOR. There are obvious downsides to letting a 6 year old loose in that kind of gaming environment, not to mention the problem of being asked &quot;Mommy read this to me&quot; every 30 seconds. I've seen the Disney Infinity Star Wars game, and frankly I can't think of anything that would make H happier than being able to run around as Ahsoka and Leia -- and at some point I am assuming, Rei. I'm guessing some of the other Disney characters would be hits with her too. But one game does not a console purchase justify, and any way it seems to be available for both X-Box and Playstation (though on Amazon it looks like the Star Wars saga pack is for PS4 only??)<br />
<br />
So, which console and which games would you buy if the primary audience is a 6 year old who turns every toy she has into a vehicle for elaborate story telling, who loves Star Wars, Dungeon (the board game), Nerf Guns, fairies and elves of all sorts, and the RPG component of SWOTOR (she really loves the dialogue choices). Additional complication -- H regards being alone as a fate worse than death, so it would be good if there are games we can play with her without wanting to kill ourselves. Or her.</div>

]]></content:encoded>
