			<title>Shadow Complex Free on PC Through December</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?78306-Shadow-Complex-Free-on-PC-Through-December&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Sat, 05 Dec 2015 02:19:09 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[This was announced at the 2015 Game Awards, but I thought I would make a thread for it for those who like free games but don't care about the other stuff in that thread. 
 
Shadow Complex is a 2D action platformer in the Metroidvania* style that was released on the 360 about six years ago, and was...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>This was announced at the 2015 Game Awards, but I thought I would make a thread for it for those who like free games but don't care about the other stuff in that thread.<br />
<br />
Shadow Complex is a 2D action platformer in the Metroidvania* style that was released on the 360 about six years ago, and was arguably one of the forerunners of digital content for the platform. It was very popular and I had always wished it would get a PC version. Now not only is it getting &quot;remastered&quot; for modern consoles, but it's got a PC version that as the title says is free through the month of December. The only caveat is that you need to download it through Epic's own game service/launcher.<br />
<br />
<a href="https://www.epicgames.com/shadowcomplex/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">https://www.epicgames.com/shadowcomplex/</a><br />
<br />
*Metroidvania refers to a style of gameplay that comes from mashing up Metroid and Castlevania styles. Instead of levels you have one expansive complex that gets mapped as you explore. Eventually you find upgrades that let you access previously inaccessible areas.<br />
<br />
<br />
Not to open a can of worms, but I will put it one disclaimer for those of you it matters to. Shadow Complex is based on the book Empire by Orson Scott Card.</div>

]]></content:encoded>
