			<title>Game Awards 2015 - Dec. 3</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?78304-Game-Awards-2015-Dec-3&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Thu, 03 Dec 2015 14:37:24 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[Here I go again, forgetting to make a thread about this until the last minute. It's time for the second year of Video Game Awards after the split with Spike TV. Last year's was pretty disorganized, but I appreciated what they were trying to do and there were definitely parts that I liked, and it...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Here I go again, forgetting to make a thread about this until the last minute. It's time for the second year of Video Game Awards after the split with Spike TV. Last year's was pretty disorganized, but I appreciated what they were trying to do and there were definitely parts that I liked, and it was a big improvement over the year prior to that. Here's hoping it improves again this year.<br />
<br />
Though, if I'm honest, one of the main reasons why I ever care about these shows at all is that for awhile they were used as an extra event to announce games, but that was becoming less true even when Spike TV ran the show, and was almost nonexistent during last year's reboot. Where before, the idea of showing off something in December was novel, the trend has spread and this show is no longer the only avenue to do such a thing with. To some, focusing on the awards and the culture itself is better and makes more sense anyway; I'll reserve further judgement. <br />
<br />
I've been distracted by Fallout 4 and haven't been following this very closely, but apparently Keighley is promising 10 Awards presented on stage, and 10 &quot;World Premiers&quot;, not new announcements necessarily, but rather new looks at upcoming games.<br />
<br />
Some of the things I've seen suggested will be shown: <br />
Tomb Raider<br />
Far Cry Primal<br />
Quantum Break<br />
Oculus Rift<br />
Walking Dead <br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
If you want to watch it: <a href="http://thegameawards.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://thegameawards.com/</a> Last year's was extremely long though, so I wouldn't blame you for waiting for the highlights.<br />
<br />
<br />
As a bonus, I can't remember if anyone ever made a thread for it when it got announced (the announcement timing was really weird), but here is the trailer for Fall Cry Primal:<br />
