			<title>Playstation Experience 2015 - Dec. 5-6</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?78303-Playstation-Experience-2015-Dec-5-6&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Thu, 03 Dec 2015 14:36:51 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[Last year I lumped this in with the Game Awards thread for simplicity, this year I gave them each their own thread to allow for more editorializing (rambling) without having to worry about thread bloat. I'm not sure the level of discussion will justify two threads, but we will try it and see...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Last year I lumped this in with the Game Awards thread for simplicity, this year I gave them each their own thread to allow for more editorializing (rambling) without having to worry about thread bloat. I'm not sure the level of discussion will justify two threads, but we will try it and see anyway. I'll still post summaries and trailers I find interesting from each of the events.<br />
<br />
Anyway, this will be the second year for the Playstation Experience. The various game companies have realized that it is beneficial to have big events showing off upcoming releases spread out across the year, instead of just being something you see at E3. Last year's show was actually kind of dull in the grand scheme of things, though I still look forward to seeing what they do this year. <br />
<br />
Having said that, I've been so preoccupied with Fallout 4 that I haven't been following any news lately and have no idea what they possibly could show. It seems a lot of what people are suggesting are the usual contenders that have yet to be shown yet but get suggested every year, either from wish fulfillment or because those studios have got to be making something. Sony Bend's next game, Santa Monica's next game (God of War), Crash Bandicoot, etc.<br />
<br />
They didn't really have many big surprises last year, so I am skeptical they would do it this year. I would expect a focus on anything likely to come out before the next E3. Uncharted 4 and Street Fighter 5 are the only games off the top of my head that meet that criteria. Sony has been working on getting PS2 emulation working on PS4 hardware. Might finally announce that. VR was big at E3 and is supposed to launch in 2016 so maybe they will have a launch date and price?<br />
<br />
Square will definitely be on stage, though whether or not they bring anything of value is a mystery. When they finally announced a FF7 remake earlier in the year they promised to tell us more in December. I don't trust them though, so it's anyone's guess what we will actually get. They've got a lot in development though, so surely they will show something, right?</div>

]]></content:encoded>
